    ///<summary>
    ///SNARK-anchored redeem (SPEC-snark-redeem-B §4.1).
    ///
    ///Public input layout, 4 × 32B = 128B:
    ///  [0..32)    root
    ///  [32..64)   nullifier
    ///  [64..96)   recipient   ( = uint256(Txn.sender.bytes) mod Fr_MOD )
    ///  [96..128)  denomination (big-endian Fr element, equals root box's denom)
    ///
    ///Error codes (§4.3):
    ///  BAD_ROOT       — rootRef not in r: registry
    ///  DOUBLE_SPEND   — nb:<nullifier> exists
    ///  BAD_RECIPIENT  — recipient public input ≠ derived(Txn.sender)
    ///  BAD_PROOF      — verifier rejected
    ///
    ///Verifier budget pooled via `ensureSnarkBudget()` (≈ 80k units / 115 OpUps).
    ///Caller must supply enough staticFee — recommended 200_000 µAlgo (see
    ///internal/benchmarks/verifier-cost.md).
    ///
    ///Recipient binding (B-lite, Tornado-style): the contract reduces
    ///`Txn.sender.bytes` (32-byte ed25519 pubkey) mod the BN254 Fr prime and
    ///asserts equality with the proof's recipient public input. Pairing soundness
    ///means a front-runner replaying the proof with their own sender derives a
    ///different recipient → BAD_RECIPIENT.
    ///</summary>
